Readings: Identity and Access Management

IAM is an Identity and access management (IAM) in enterprise IT is about defining and managing the roles and accesses to privileges of individual network users and the circumstances in which users are granted or even denied to those with privileges. The core objective of IAM systems is one digital identity per individual. IAM tools include password-management tools, provisioning software apps and identity repositories, security-policy enforcement applications, reporting and monitoring apps and identity repositories. 


